<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About Us — Demo Bank</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
 <div class="banner">Demo project — fictional bank for coursework</div>
  <% if (loggedIn) { %>
    <%- include('partials/navbar', { active: 'about' }) %>
  <% } else { %>
    <%- include('partials/public-nav') %>
  <% } %>

  <div class="page-wrap">
    <div class="card">
      <h1 class="page-title">About Demo Bank</h1>
      <p>
        Demo Bank is a fictional banking dashboard built as a student project.
        It exists to demonstrate core web development skills — authentication,
        server-rendered pages, forms, and an admin/user permission split —
        using a banking theme as the subject matter.
      </p>
      <p>
        No part of this site is connected to a real financial institution,
        payment processor, or real user funds. Every balance, transaction,
        and account number shown here is fictional data created for this
        class project.
      </p>
      <h2 class="section-title">What this project demonstrates</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>User authentication with hashed passwords (bcrypt)</li>
        <li>Role-based access: regular user dashboard vs. admin panel</li>
        <li>An auditable log of every balance change (who, when, why)</li>
        <li>Linked multi-page navigation (Home, About, Contact, Loan, Settings, Notifications)</li>
        <li>Form handling and server-side rendering with EJS</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>